          <p>The naturalist Henry David Thoreau once wrote of water that it is the “finest worker” in industry: “the gentle touches of air and water working at their leisure,” he wrote, can do more to shape rocks and space than even the most well-whittled tools or metals like copper and bronze. <a href="/iiot-at-work/stories/bellagio-fountains">Read more.</a></p>
